Class NamedObjId

  • java.lang.Object
    • ptolemy.kernel.util.NamedObj

        • ptolemy.kernel.util.AbstractSettableAttribute
          • ptolemy.kernel.util.StringAttribute
            • org.kepler.moml.NamedObjId
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, Changeable, ChangeListener, Debuggable, DebugListener, Derivable, ModelErrorHandler, MoMLExportable, Moveable, Nameable, Settable

    public class NamedObjId
extends StringAttribute
implements ChangeListener
    The NamedObjId is a StringAttribute to be used for identifying a NamedObj by a KeplerLSID. A NamedObj that contains this Attribute is considered to be uniquely identified by the KeplerLSID that this NamedObjId stores. This class also handles the updating of KeplerLSIDs based on the ptolemy change listener system. Static methods in org.kepler.objectmanager.ObjectManager can be used to access NamedObjId attributes contained by NamedObjs.
    Author:
    berkley, schultz
    Created:
    March 1, 2005
